rComments: Gerry has been one of the best profs I have ever had in my life. His course was super interesting, and he did an excellent job teaching. Also, he is a super, super nice man and fun to talk to. 11/10 would recommend

His classes are straight forward and easy to follow. His tests are pretty much exactly what we learn in class....I love his jokes! He has a great sense of humour.  He will throw in the occasional "dad joke". Too be honest sometimes the jokes are so bland I can't help but laugh. He is a really nice guy and always is helpful if you have a question :)

He's a genius! Like a walking textbook. Absolutely incredible lectures, makes all material so clear and tests fair. Hilarious dry sense of humour. Hope to have him for my second semester Anat&Phys. Best prof I've ever had!
Knows his stuff and teaches in a way that you will always get it

Gerry is the best prof I have ever had at U of T. He is such a nice and approachable man! If you miss a test or quiz, he is very accomodating and always says that if you aren't ready to write the quiz then you should wait until you are ready. I wish I could take his course every year!
A very helpful, approachable, and enthusiastic instructor.

I love this prof. He is really passionate about the material, but in such a dry humorous way, its really cute. He is really nice and helpful and understanding. Course (eeb263) is really hard, but he does use nice easy diagrams.

Professor Gerry is a great guy. He likes his students a lot, and if you put in the time to learn the material you'll do well. The labs are pretty tough, but do well in the quizes and prepare adequately for the lab quizes (lots of time in the lab and memorizing things) you're set.
Knows his material but does not show any real enthusiasm for what he teaches. Expects you to know material without really any devices for visual learners.
memorize everything and maybe you can pass, the labs were hell

"Doctor Gerry" was very helpful and intelligent prof. A lot of the students in our (Practical Nursing) Anatomy class had very little knowledge prior to taking the class, and that changed quickly. Dispite the fact that he probably never learned my name, he treated me (in my ignorance) with respect when I asked questions. Good prof.

awesome proff, very clear, good diagrams and he'll actually tell you what's on the test. Super nice and more than resonable when it comes to marking. However, we could never could get him to drink with us though...
is very nice and seems to like the students. Dry sense of humour- pretty funny...would take this course over for sure!

Covers a lot of material but isn't boring. Will know your name within 4 lectures, so look out (no anonymity)! Lectures without powerpoint, which is fine, but if you're not a fast writer an audio recorder would be very helpful. Fair tests if you study and go to (and keep up in) lab!
While the material is very difficult, De Iuliis is an excellent professor and is mindful of all his students, even those who do not do well.
Very helpfuL, funny, and fair.                 GO LEAFS GO!!!!!!!!!!!
He's very fair but expects you to know a great deal, but if you study well, you'll guarenteed to do good. Very clear speaker with a great sense of humour (go Leafs go!! haha)
Good Sense of humour, even with the lame jokes haha.  Very approachable and really knows his subject!  A great Prof.!
